ers (1)''': [[FA Youth Cup Finals of the 1960s|1967\u201368]]\n\n[[The Central League#Central League Cup|'''Central League Cup''']] '''(North)'''\n* '''Winners (1)''': 2015\u201316\n\n'''[[Lancashire Senior Cup]]'''\n* '''Winners (12)''': 1889\u201390, 1914\u201315, 1949\u201350, 1951\u201352, 1959\u201360, 1960\u201361, 1961\u201362, 1964\u201365, 1965\u201366, 1969\u201370, 1971\u201372, 1992\u201393\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Graduates==\nBurnley officially recognises that the first players to graduate through the youth system were [[Tommy Lawton]] and [[Ken Ashbridge]] during the [[1936\u201337 Burnley F.C. season|1936\u201337 season]]. Below is a list of all the players that have gone on to play the first team since 1936.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.uptheclarets.com/players/burnley-fc-youth-academy|title=Burnley FC Youth Academy Graduates|last=Scholes|first=Tony|date=15 September 2016|website=UpTheClarets|access-date=22 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nPlayers that have been capped at full international level are in '''bold'''.\n{|\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top;\"\n||\n1930s\n*'''{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tommy Lawton]]'''\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Ken Ashbridge]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Len Martindale]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Freddy Taylor]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[George Bray]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[George Knight (footballer, born 1921)|George Knight]]\n||\n1940s\n*'''{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Peter Kippax (footballer)|Peter Kippax]]'''\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Harry Mather]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Harry Potts]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Harold Spencer]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Harold Rudman]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} Jack Knight\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tommy Cummings]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tommy Henderson (footballer, born 1927)|Tommy Henderson]]\n||\n1950s\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Roy Stephenson]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jimmy Adamson]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tony Hapgood]]\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Albert Cheesebrough]]\n*'''{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Brian Pilkington (footballer)|Brian Pilkington]]'''\n*{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Doug Winton]]\n*{{fl